The ANC has described Northern Cape P remier Sylvia Lucas&#8217; decision to reshuffle her provincial cabinet as &#8221; a flagrant abuse of her office &#8220;.On Wednesday Lucas announced the reshuffle ahead of the party &#8217; s Provincial Conference.&#8221; We view this as a flagrant abuse of her office to further divide the ANC and undermine unity of the organisation,&#8221;&#8221; Her unbridled arrogance is a betrayal of trust with the ANC &#8211; the organisation that deployed her as Premier,&#8221; said the ANC in a statement.ANC provincial secretary Zamani Saul has previously stated that the party was not consulted before the decision was taken.-TNA Reporter 